A '''combat only pure''', or '''reverse skiller''', is a type of pure that only develops [[combat]] skills and the [[Slayer]] skill. Combat pures keep their skilling stats at level 1, leaving them with a max [[total level]] of 807. This makes it more challenging to acquire gear or progress the account as some regions of [[Gielinor]] are not accessible, and some content or gear requires [[quests]] with skilling involved.

A combat only account type can be played on any [[Ironman Mode|game mode]] but it is most recommended as a [[Ironman Mode|Hardcore Ironman]], [[Ironman Mode|Regular Ironman]], or [[Ironman Mode|Ultimate Ironman]]. Each mode will bring their own unique flavour to how a combat only pure progresses their account. As a reminder to those who choose [[Ironman Mode|Ultimate Ironman]], it is possible to "downgrade" an [[Ironman Mode|Ultimate Ironman]] to a normal [[Ironman Mode|Ironman]] or [[Main account|main]] account by talking to the [[Iron Man tutor]] in [[Lumbridge]].

This page has a quick introduction to the combat only build, as well as some guidance on getting started on a new combat only account. The guide is broken down to three stages of the game (Early-game, Mid-game, and End-game), each with their own article providing more details. The links are below each respective section of this page. It is highly recommended to read the early- and mid-game sections before starting the account to get a good idea of what progression will look like and pick some goals to set for yourself.

''Throughout the guide keep an eye out for this icon [[File:Dungeon icon.png|frameless|link=https://oldschool.runescape.wiki/w/File:Dungeon_icon.png]] as it might be important to maintain account integrity.''

__TOC__

==[[File:Dungeon icon.png|frameless]] Restrictions==
Before getting started as a combat only pure, it is important to understand some of the unique restrictions that come with the build. Alongside the [[Ironman_Mode#Restrictions|restrictions]] given to every [[Ironman|Ironman]], [[Ironman Mode|Ultimate Ironmen]], or [[Ironman Mode|Hardcore Ironman]], combat only pures avoid the following:
*Cannot level any skilling stat to 2 or more.
*Cannot complete quests that reward the player with skilling XP outside of combat, or [[Slayer]]. 
*Cannot access [[Tirannwn]], [[Piscatoris Fishing Colony]], [[Miscellania]], [[Fremennik Isles]], [[Trollweiss Mountain]], [[Weiss]], [[Darkmeyer]], [[Burgh de Rott]], [[Sophanem]], [[Kharazi Jungle]], [[Ape Atoll]], [[Crandor]], and many other small quest specific areas.
*Cannot unlock [[Chivalry]], or [[Piety]] prayers.
*Cannot build inside of their [[Player-owned house|house]]. You can still buy a house in [[Rimmington]] to teleport to and place a [[Wintumber tree|Wintumber Tree]].
*Potion and food supplies are limited. 
*No slayer cape because [[Duradel]] is skill locked 
*(Currently) No access to [[God Wars Dungeon]]
Other than these areas, most content like [[Barrows]], [[Chambers of Xeric]], [[Theatre of Blood]], [[Inferno]], [[Wilderness]], [[Boss|Slayer bosses]], and some [[quests]] are available to complete. For more information on everything available, see the equipment progression table and account guides below.

===Tips===
Below are some of the most important combat only tips that will help you progress easier and avoid ruining the account build.

*[[File:Dungeon icon.png|frameless]] Always carry a [[File:Cadantine.png|frameless]] [[Cadantine|clean cadantine]] to exchange for a [[File:Super restore(4).png|frameless]] [[super restore]] potion during the [[Jekyll and Hyde|Jekyll]] random event. You can clean grimy herbs in [[Nardah]] for 200 gp by talking to [[Zahur]]. Stockpile these for your first [[fire cape]] run. 
* [[File:Dungeon icon.png|frameless]] Never start [[Dragon Slayer I]]. (It unlocks dragon tasks by just starting it. You can, however, still enter the [[Champions' Guild]].)
*[[File:Dungeon icon.png|frameless]] Never do Death Plateau. (Will unlock tasks like [[Spiritual creature|Spiritual Creatures]], [[Troll|Stronghold Trolls]] from [[Konar quo Maten|Konar]], and [[God Wars Dungeon]] [[Bloodveld|bloodvelds]] from [[Konar quo Maten|Konar]].)
* [[File:Dungeon icon.png|frameless]] Remember to pick up and keep multiple extra [[File:Magic whistle.png|frameless]] [[Magic whistle|magic whistles]] and [[File:Holy table napkin.png|frameless]] [[Holy table napkin|holy table napkins]] during the Holy Grail quest. [[Ironman Mode|Ultimate Ironmen]] should stop after ''"I should follow him the the Castle to get the Holy Grail"'' text in the quest log. (Requirement to return to the [[Fisher Realm]] for a hard clue step.)
* [[File:Dungeon icon.png|frameless]] Never do the [[ScapeRune|Bob ScapeRune]] random events. The fishing one rewards the player with either Fishing or Magic XP potentially ruining the combat only build.
* [[File:Dungeon icon.png|frameless]] Always double check quest rewards before starting or completing a quest.
*[[File:Dungeon icon.png|frameless]] Use every XP lamp on Prayer.
*[[File:Dungeon icon.png|frameless]] If doing pre-75 combat Slayer, don't complete [[Ernest the Chicken]] or [[Priest in Peril]] to avoid bad tasks.
*[[File:Dungeon icon.png|frameless]] Be careful with [[Chambers of Xeric]] [[Corrupted scavenger|thieving chests]]. They give a minimum of 40 XP if misclicked. (Toggle your run energy on/off to cancel thieving the chest.)
*[[File:Dungeon icon.png|frameless]] Be careful with the [[Nature Grotto]] medium/hard clue step bridge jump. It has a chance to give 15 XP on success or 2 XP on fail (25-30% chance of success).

==[[File:Quest_point_icon.png|frameless]] Quests==
The following [[quests]] can be completed by combat only pures as they do not reward the player with any experience points in skills that would level the stat to 2.

Finishing all of these quests would require the skill levels in the box to the right and leave you with 58 [[quest points]]. Most combat only pures skip some quests due to undesirable [[Slayer task]] unlocks after completion (such as [[Spiritual creature|spiritual creatures]] from [[Death Plateau]] or dragon tasks from starting Dragon Slayer I).

